The **Endgame** is a [defunct](/wiki/Defunct_features "Defunct features") level that existed from [NetHack 3.0.0](/wiki/NetHack_3.0.0 "NetHack 3.0.0") to [NetHack 3.0.10](/wiki/NetHack_3.0.10 "NetHack 3.0.10"). It is the precursor to the [Astral Plane](/wiki/Astral_Plane "Astral Plane") introduced in [NetHack 3.1.0](/wiki/NetHack_3.1.0 "NetHack 3.1.0") as part of the current [End Game](/wiki/End_Game "End Game").

The above core of the level is surrounded by a maze. Because the walls are undiggable, the only entrance is via the marked [secret doors](/wiki/Secret_door "Secret door"). Upon entry, the player must pass through seven chambers containing, in order, five random R (which, in practice, will always be [rust monsters](/wiki/Rust_monster "Rust monster")), six random L, five random N, eight random D and four [krakens](/wiki/Kraken "Kraken"), five random H, six random O, and five random T. The final chamber contains a secret door which leads to a corridor connecting three islands, each with an [altar](/wiki/Altar "Altar") of a different alignment. As in the current version, the amulet must be offered on the correct altar in order to win the game.
